track_notes: Oct 3 2020: Most of the trail is pretty easy to follow.  At times though, especially in the upper section, the trail fades and is marked by numerous cairns. At the time of this writing the sign at the trailhead is erroneous, stating the roundtrip distance is 12 miles.  It is NOT!  It is about 5.5 miles (measured).  There are a few switchbacks, but the trail is not overly steep and there is good footing throughout.  The summit has plenty of trees, an ammo box with climber log and reference maps, nice views.  The trail goes through a few burned sections.  In summary, quiet, pleasant, moderate hike. de K7ZOO

The area has so many dirt roads I felt it would be helpful to include driving directions.  From Colorado City AZ the drive is about 60 miles of dirt road.  Ramsays Auto in Kanab UT will retrieve you for $165/hour (I only bought a tire there.)  This route is NOT RECOMMENDED except if you have something like a Jeep.  I drive a Subaru Forester, and there is a stretch of deep silt / sand at N36° 31.197 W113° 03.150.  The eastern side of the road was higher and seemed like the better side to drive.  My Suburau made it pretty easily through the sand, but 2WD or low clearance would be very sketchy.  Other than that spot, the dirt roads are very well maintained, even with an occasional road sign (amazing).  Local authorities recommend taking along a couple of full-sized spare tires -- I would concur... you are a long ways from rescue services.  While camped there I was able to engage a local 2m FM repeater in St George UT 146.82- PL100; use a 3-el yagi. de K7ZOO
track_title: NOT RECOMMENDED -- heavy silt at one point

track_notes: At this time (Oc t 2020) this was a very good road, well-maintained dirt the entire length.  Some washboarding, a few areas with rough rocks, and some cattle on the road.  de K7ZOO

There are a couple primitive campsites about 100 yards SE of the trailhead.  These are very convenient to the trailhead, but I choose a location with less traffic.  At the beginning of this track is an area off the dirt road that served me well as a campsite.  The only signficant traffic:  at night there were a handful of off-road vehicles literally RACING around the Mt Trumbul areas; during the day an occasional pickup truck or large working truck. Easy to hit the 146.82- PL100 repeater in St George with a 3-el yagi. No cell service.  de K7ZOO
track_title: Two Campsite Options for W7A NM001
